| Kernel Type        | Formula (General Idea)                 | Use Case / Shape Detected                                 |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Linear**         | $K(x, y) = x^\top y$                   | Same as regular PCA (no real kernel effect).              |
| **Polynomial**     | $K(x, y) = (x^\top y + c)^d$           | Detects **curved** and **multi-order** relationships.     |
| **RBF / Gaussian** | $K(x, y) = \exp(-\gamma \|x - y\|^2)$  | Great for **complex nonlinear** and **local** structures. |
| **Sigmoid**        | $K(x, y) = \tanh(\alpha x^\top y + c)$ | Used in neural networks; less common in PCA.              |


ðŸ“Œ Standard PCA (No Kernel): Fails on nonlinear patterns, e.g., concentric circles.
